social_posts.post_text: zalympix & lunch with my sister in the same day ⛽️💨💨 “life is good”

These girls have further annhilated my highly distressed handwoven rug (hereon referred to as “rug”) and while my tolerance for their collective shanenigans has been tried once, twice, and more than likely again soon in our imminent futures— I, Krit A. McClean, have decided, on this Friday of Cinco de Mayo in LA (05/05/2023), to rescind my ownership and attachment, both emotional and physical, to said 8.7’ x 11.1’ rug, and hereby declare that this asset, in its entirety of all its threads of wool, silk, and suede, shall henceforth be transferred with regard to title, value, and liability to the following domesticated mammals, in equal ownshership, i.e. in sums representing a 50-50 equity split in the form of 50 shares each totaling 100, to Bambi I. McClean and Darci I. McClean-Hunt.
